playlist_videos.title: Baby Taku's World - I Love My Daddy Song - ChuChu TV Sing-along Nursery Rhymes for Babies & Kids
playlist_videos.description:
The "I Love My Daddy" song is all about celebrating the awesome bond between a dad and his little one. It's all about how Baby Taku shows love and thanks to his dad while they take on everyday challenges together. The song really captures their growing love and the happiness it brings to them both. So, come join this cute pair on their journey filled with love, laughter, and endless joy.

You can listen to this song on your preferred music streaming platforms. - https://orcd.co/ilovemydaddy

Baby Taku's World - I Love You Daddy Song Lyrics:

I love my daddy
My daddy loves me too
He takes such good care of me
I wonder what I can do

I want him to know
That he is special to me
I’ll find a way to show him
Without him even knowing

Daddy is tired
He’s working very hard
I’ll make sure he gets rest
Daddy deserves the best

Huh?
Do you know who did this?

Daddy’s looks  unhappy
He can’t find what he needs
I secretly will find it
And put it where he’ll see

Huh?
How did this happen?
Do you know who put it here?

When Daddy gets a boo-boo
And he is feeling blue
I’ll stay right by his side
And my love I will provide

I will kiss his boo-boo
And make it go away
He helps me when I’m hurt
And I’ll always do the same

I think someone made  my boo-boo go away
Do you know who it could be?

 He he he
Ha ha ha ha

I know who’s been helping
And doing things for me
You are my little buddy
You make me so happy

I’m one happy daddy
I have the best baby
I'm always there for him
And he's always there for me

Ha ha ha ha ha ha

playlist_videos.title: Baby Taku's World - Strongest Animals Song - ChuChu TV Sing-along Nursery Rhymes
playlist_videos.description:
"Strongest Animal Song" is an awe-inspiring song that highlights the strength of various animals. Each creature mentioned in our song will amaze you, from the mighty Grizzly bear to the industrious Dung beetle. Join us on a journey through the animal kingdom and discover why they are more strong.

Baby Taku's World - Strongest Animals Song

Animals are so strong, you see.
Stronger than you and me.
Let’s meet some, I’ll show you now.
They’ll make you go; wow, wow, wow!
Wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow!
Wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow!

The Grizzly bear is a strong fella.
The Grizzly can carry hundreds of pounds!
Anaconda is so long like a bus.
Anaconda’s body squeeze; crush, crush, crush !

The Elephant’s the biggest animal on land.
The Elephant is way stronger than any man.
The Musk ox can carry lots of weight.
The Musk ox is really great!
Wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow!
Wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow, wow!

The Tiger looks sharp in his stripes.
His muscles are full of might.
The Eagle is the strongest bird,
a very powerful predator.

The Gorilla is super strong.
The Gorilla’s arms are sturdy and long.

playlist_videos.description:
In this heartwarming song, Baby Taku helps his mom recover from an injury with the love and support of his family.

Mommy has a Boo-Boo Song Lyrics :

Poor Mommy has a boo-boo! 
Ouch, ouch!

Poor Mommy has a boo-boo! 

Oh, dear!

Dear Mommy has to rest
She has to stay in bed
Will you, will you help her rest? 

We will!

We’ll help with all the little, little chores

For sure!
Pick up things that are lying on the floor

For sure!
Take the laundry off the line
Make sure things are neat and nice
Do our best so that Mommy can rest

We’ll tidy up our room, make our beds

Oh, yes
We’ll put away our toys, clear the mess

No mess
Help Daddy dust and sweep
So that Mommy can sleep
Do our best, so that Mommy can rest!

We’ll tiptoe round the house, shh, shh!

Shh, shh!
We’ll be quiet as a mouse

Shh, shh!
If we let her sleep tight
Mommy will wake up feeling bright
Do our best, so that Mommy can rest!

We’ll show her lots of care and love

Care and love!
Let her know we love her very much

Very much!
We’ll do little things for her
That will make her happier
Do our best, so that Mommy can rest! 

My boo-boo is gone now 
I feel fine
Thank you for taking such good care of me, my darlings!

playlist_videos.description:
So, in this song, Baby Taku gets a new friend, but this one's imaginary and totally cute! The friend only comes to life when Baby Taku is around and switches back to toy mode when others show up. The song is all about the adorable bond between Baby Taku and the imaginary friend.

Click here to Subscribe to our channel - https://bit.ly/32NxN7y

Baby Taku's World - My Imaginary Friend song Lyrics :

Meet Baby’s friend, a very special friend
He is Baby’s imaginary friend
He talks with me; and plays with me
But I’m the only one who can see
Shhhhhh!

Who were you talking to, Baby? 
There’s no one here!

He goes everywhere that Baby goes
He is always right under Baby’s nose
He’s not just a toy; he’s like a real boy
But that’s something nobody knows
Shhhhhh!

Huh? 
That was fast! 
Well done, Baby!

When Mommy is around, he is very still
Mommy doesn’t know his special skill
When Mommy isn’t there, he is everywhere
But that’s our little secret so you can’t spill 
Shhhhhh!

He is such a naughty little one
Full of mischief, full of fun
He spills my milk, he makes such a mess
And everyone says, “Look what Baby’s done!” 

Oh, Baby! 
Look at what you’ve done!

playlist_videos.title: Yes Yes Go to School Song - ChuChu TV Baby Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs Baby Taku’s World  #BabyTaku
playlist_videos.description:
This song is available to listen on all music streaming platforms.- https://orcd.co/chuchutvhits

Baby Taku is feeling lazy about going to school. However, his mother encourages him to establish good habits, such as waking up early, brushing his teeth, taking a nice bath, dressing neatly, eating healthily, and enjoying his time at school. 

Lyrics :

Wake up, wake up, wake up dear
It's time to go to school
No, no, no, mommy
I can't get up so soon

Wake up, wake up, wake up dear
The birds are chirping with love
Yes, yes, yes mommy
I will wake up now

Brush, brush, brush your teeth
It's time to go to school
No, no, no, mommy
It's a boring thing to do

Brush, brush, brush your teeth
To keep the germs out
Yes, yes, yes mommy
I will brush my teeth now

Bathe, bathe, bathe my dear
It's time to go to school
No, no, no, no, no mommy
I feel so cold

Look, look, look at the ducks
Say quack, quack, quack
Yes, yes, yes mommy
I will take a bath

Dress, dress, get dressed dear
It's time to go to school
No, no, no, mommy
I don't want to change my clothes

Look, look, look at your sister
She’s all dressed for school
Yes, yes, yes mommy
I will get dressed too

Eat, eat, eat your breakfast
It's time to go to school
No, no, no, no, no, no mommy
I don't like this food

Look, look, look at your brother
He’s enjoying his food
Yes, yes, yes mommy
I will eat and be good

The bus, bus, bus is here
To take you all to school
Yes, yes, yes mommy
We’re ready to go to school

playlist_videos.description:
Have fun listening to ChuChu TV's songs on Spotify: https://chuchu.me/Spotify

Baby Taku and his friends sometimes get hurt and suffer boo-boos while playing. It's heartwarming to see how their mothers lovingly comfort them and help them feel better.
The Boo Boo Song Lyrics:

My dear mommy when I was running out
A tiny little bumble bee flew right by my mouth
I got scared and fell right in the dirt
Now I’ve got a Boo-boo and it really hurts

Oh! my dear baby let me look at you
Mommy knows how to deal with Your Boo-boo
A Bandage on the Boo-boo will make it all right
Now you can go and play again until it is night

My dear mommy I was jumping there
Suddenly a little train came out of nowhere
I hopped on the train and landed on my toe
Now I got a Boo-boo can you make it go?

Dear little baby let me look at you
Mommy knows how to deal with Your Boo-boo
A bandage on the Boo-boo will make it all right
Now you can jump again to the left and to the right

Ah! Dear mommy when I was playing ball
It hit me in the back after bouncing on the wall
I fell down hard and scratched my hand, I’m not quite sure how
Please save me from this painful Boo-boo now

Baby don’t you cry, let me look at you
Mommy knows how to heal the Boo-boo
We’ll wash and add some cream to make the Boo-boo all right
Now my baby can play, You’re all right

Lovely little babies want to play and play
Sometimes an obstactle gets in their way
A fall can cause a boo-boo and give them quite a fright
But then mommies fix the boo-boo’s and make it all alright

Baby Taku really wants to stay in bed, but ChuChu, ChaCha, Mommy, and Daddy wake him up with a super cheerful song to get him excited for the day! It's time for Baby Taku to wake up and join in the fun!

Lyrics:

Wake Up, Wake Up
Wake Up, Wake Up, Wake Up, My Dear!
The chirping Of Birds Is Nice To Hear!
Look At Your Kittens & Play With Cheer!
It's Time To Wake Up, Oh! My Dear!

No, No, Dear Mommy, Let Me Sleep!
Let Me Sleep! Let Me SLEEP!

Wake Up, Wake Up, Wake Up, My Child!
Welcome the Dawn That's So Bright!
Sun Is Rising And Spreading Its Light!
It's Time To Enjoy This Beautiful Sight!

No, No, Dear Daddy, Let Me Sleep!
Let Me Sleep! Let Me SLEEP!

Puppies Are Calling, 'Woof, Woof, Woof'!
Roaster Is Calling, 'Cock-A-Doodle, Doodle, Doo'!
Cow Is Calling, 'Moo, Moo, Moo'!
Kittens Are Calling, 'Meow, Meow, Meow'!

It's Time For Me To Join Them Too!
I want to go Play With Them Now!

playlist_videos.description:
Have fun listening to ChuChu TV's songs on Spotify: https://chuchu.me/Spotify

Baby Taku, ChuChu, and ChaCha are so excited to help their dear father with different tasks. They work together to scrub and wash his car until it sparkles like new. Afterwards, they cheerfully help Daddy with the gardening and even join him in building a beautiful bird feeder.

Helping Daddy Song Lyrics :

Daddy, daddy, we love you! 
Daddy, daddy, we want to help you! 
Daddy, daddy, let us help too! 

Let’s clean the car, my darlings! 
Scrub the car, that’s what we’ll do! 
Wash the car, that’s what we’ll do! 
Polish the car, that’s what we’ll do! 
The car’s now clean, my darlings! 

Daddy, daddy, we love you! 
Daddy, daddy, we want to help you! 
Daddy, Daddy, let us help too! 

Let’s do some gardening, my darlings! 
Rake the leaves, that’s what we’ll do! 
Mow the lawn, that’s what we’ll do! 
Water the flowers, that’s what we’ll do! 
The garden looks lovely, my darlings! 

Daddy, daddy, we love you! 
Daddy, daddy, we want to help you! 
Daddy, daddy, let us help too! 

We’ll feed the birds, my darlings! 
We’ll paint a can, that’s what we’ll do. 
Hang it up, that’s what we’ll do. 
Fill in seeds, that’s what we’ll do. 
The bird feeder’s ready, my darlings! 

Daddy, daddy, we love you! 
Daddy, daddy, we had fun with you! 
Daddy, daddy, there’s no one like you! 
I love you too, my darlings!

Baby Taku, ChuChu, and ChaCha are so excited to help their dear father with different tasks. They work together to scrub and wash his car until it sparkles like new. Afterwards, they cheerfully help Daddy with the gardening and even join him in building a beautiful bird feeder.

Helping Daddy Song Lyrics :

Daddy, daddy, we love you! 
Daddy, daddy, we want to help you! 
Daddy, daddy, let us help too! 

Let’s clean the car, my darlings! 
Scrub the car, that’s what we’ll do! 
Wash the car, that’s what we’ll do! 
Polish the car, that’s what we’ll do! 
The car’s now clean, my darlings! 

Daddy, daddy, we love you! 
Daddy, daddy, we want to help you! 
Daddy, Daddy, let us help too! 

Let’s do some gardening, my darlings! 
Rake the leaves, that’s what we’ll do! 
Mow the lawn, that’s what we’ll do! 
Water the flowers, that’s what we’ll do! 
The garden looks lovely, my darlings! 

Daddy, daddy, we love you! 
Daddy, daddy, we want to help you! 
Daddy, daddy, let us help too! 

We’ll feed the birds, my darlings! 
We’ll paint a can, that’s what we’ll do. 
Hang it up, that’s what we’ll do. 
Fill in seeds, that’s what we’ll do. 
The bird feeder’s ready, my darlings! 

Daddy, daddy, we love you!

Daddy, daddy, there’s no one like you! 
I love you too, my darlings!

playlist_videos.description:
Have fun listening to ChuChu TV's songs on Spotify: https://chuchu.me/Spotify

When Baby Taku and his friends are having fun playing, sometimes their toys can get boo-boos. Luckily, ChuChu, ChaCha, and all the older kids are there to cheer up the babies and help make the toys all better.

Toy Gets a Boo Boo Lyrics :

Teddy bear and I were playing on the seesaw
Teddy bear fell down and hurt his little paw
Teddy bear’s got a boo-boo, he’s growling in pain
Oh, I wish that teddy bear would feel better again!

Poor little teddy bear looks so sad and blue
But don’t you worry, we’ll fix his boo-boo!
A little bandage on him will do the trick!
Teddy bear’s smiling now, he’s feeling very fit!

Choo choo train was working very well
Someone knocked her down and bam she fell
Some of choo choo train’s wheels have come right out
Poor train’s got a boo-boo, she can’t move about

I know how to fix your little train
The tools from my toolbox will ease all her pain
We’ll put the tiny wheels back on and make them nice and tight
Oh, look at little choo choo now, she’s ready for a ride!

Friendly mister robot was walking smart and tall
But puppy dashed into him while he was chasing a ball
Mister robot’s antenna snapped right in two
He’s feeling sad now, he’s also got a boo-boo!

Mister robot’s antenna is broken, oh, oh, oh
We’ll make a new one with some modelling dough
We’ll make a nice new antenna with our very own hands, hey
Look at mister robot now, doesn’t he look grand?

All our little ones have a favorite toy
Their toys bring them lots of joy
All the toys feel so real, just like they are our friends
If they get a boo-boo we’ll give them a good mend!

playlist_videos.title: No No Brush My Teeth Song - ChuChu TV Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs #BabyTaku
playlist_videos.description:
Have fun listening to ChuChu TV's songs on Spotify: https://chuchu.me/Spotify

Baby Taku is not too keen on brushing his teeth, but his mommy, daddy, ChuChu and ChaCha tell him how important it is to keep his teeth healthy, clean, and germ-free.

No No Brush My Teeth Song Lyrics :

Come little baby brush your teeth
Let us make them clean and white
Brushing will keep the germs out of sight!
Brush up, brush down and left to right!

No dear mommy - not today
I brushed my teeth yesterday

Ah… Aha…

Don’t be lazy, oh my child
In between your teeth, germs hide
Use your toothbrush to brush them aside
Now your smile is bright and wide

Germs can come or stay or go
They are my friends don’t you know

Ah… Oh…

The germs will start to decay your teeth
Then cavities will go very deep
You’ll feel pain in your gums and teeth as well
It will hurt and your breath will smell

Oh... Oh... Oh...
No biscuit, no chocolate and no ice cream
No candy, no cake and no sweet cream
You won’t be able to eat anything sweet
And the dentist is who you will have to meet

Oh! Oh! Oh! These germs are so mean
I will keep my teeth very clean
I will brush in the morning and at night
My teeth will always be shining and bright

playlist_videos.description:
After Baby Taku returns from school, his mom inspires him to cultivate positive habits, such as cleaning up, engaging in outdoor play, consuming nutritious meals, diligently brushing his teeth every night, changing into fresh night clothes, and retiring to bed early.

Yes Yes Back from School Song Lyrics :

Welcome, welcome, welcome home, baby
Welcome back from school.
Here come brother and sister,
the day’s over so soon.

Wash, wash, wash your face,
change into clean clothes.
No, no, no, mommy,
I’m watching my favourite shows.

Look, look, look at brother,
he’s clean and refreshed.
Yes, yes, yes, mommy,
I’ll wash and get dressed.

Play, play, play, go out,
breathe the fresh cool air.
No, no, no, mommy,
I’m rocking on my chair.

Play, play, play, new games,
friends are lots of fun.
Yes, yes, yes, mommy,
I’ll play with everyone.

Eat, eat, eat, your supper,
eat the vegetables,
No, no, no, mommy,
I want chocolate cake.

Look, look, look at your brother;
he eats healthy food.
Yes, yes, yes, mommy,
they taste very good!

Change, change, change, your clothes,
time for your pajamas.
No, no, no, mommy,
let’s watch the twinkling stars.

Look, look, look at your sister,
She’s wearing her nightclothes.
Yes, yes, yes, mommy,
I will change too.

Brush, brush, brush, your teeth,
make them clean and bright.
No, no, no, mommy,
let’s dance in the moonlight.

Brushing, brushing, makes teeth clean;
it keeps the germs away.
Yes, yes, yes, mommy,
I’ll brush twice a day.

Good night, good night, good night, baby
it’s time for bed.
No, no, no, mommy,
let’s play with teddy bear.

Sleep, sleep, sleep, my baby,
I’ll sing you lullabies.
Yes, yes, yes, mommy,
I’ll close my little eyes.

Good night, sweet dreams, baby,
dream of lovely things.
Yes, yes, yes, mommy,
I’ll sleep until it’s morning.

La, la, la, lala
Lala, lala, la
Lala, lala, lala, lala
Lala, lala, la
La, lala, lala, la!
La, lala, lala, laaaa!

playlist_videos.title: Baby Goes Fishing Song - ChuChu TV Baby Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs
playlist_videos.description:
Have fun listening to ChuChu TV's songs on Spotify: https://chuchu.me/Spotify

Baby Taku, ChuChu, and ChaCha's father takes them on an exciting fishing trip to the lake. After successfully catching some fish, the children are moved by the sight of other creatures in the lake missing their friends. Touched by empathy, the kids decide to release the fish back into their natural habitat, teaching a valuable lesson about compassion and respect for all living beings.
Baby Goes Fishing Song Lyrics :

Let’s go fishing, 
Dear daddy 
Come on, come on, come on! 
The sun is bright and shiny 

Dragonflies and leaping frogs 
All around the lake 
Mother nature has made them 
Don’t they look so great? 

Friendly fish of every kind 
Jumping in and out 
Catch, catch, catch them 
Come on, pull them out 

Smiling ducks, swans and geese, 
Swim with webbed feet 
They all make pretty pictures 
They are cute and sweet 

Let’s sit by the shore 
And eat some snacks 
We’ll watch the frogs leap 
And listen to the duck’s quack 

Croak, croak, quack and quack 
The frogs and ducks say 
The fish are their friends 
They want the fish to stay 
Shall we let the fish go? 
They look so sad 
Let’s put them back 
And make them all glad 
Hee hee 
Hee hee 
Hooray! 

We had so much fun 
With our lake friends today 
Let’s go home now 
And come back another day 

Let’s go fish, fishing, 
It’s a lot of fun! 
Come with us fishing! 
Come with us, everyone!

playlist_videos.title: First Day of School Song - ChuChu TV Baby Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs
playlist_videos.description:
Baby Taku feels a bit anxious about his first day of school. However, his mommy assures him that he will discover fascinating things from his teachers, enjoy playing with various toys, and make new friends. This reassures Baby Taku and builds his excitement for school.

First Day of School Song Lyrics :

Hi, I am Baby Taku.
I love to play with my family and friends,
and I love to play with my toys.
I love coloring and playing at the park.
School? Mmm... I'll go to school soon.
I am excited but a little nervous too.
Do you want to hear about my first day of school?

It’s the first day of school
first day of school
What will I do in school?
Tell me, mommy!

You will have lots of fun,
have lots of fun, have lots of fun
You’ll meet many sweet little friends
just like you, baby

You will meet friendly teachers,
friendly teachers, friendly teachers
They’ll be very nice, my dear
Don’t worry, baby

You will learn the a, b, c’s
a, b, c’s, a, b, c’s!
And learn numbers one, two, three!
One, two, three!

You will learn lots of colors, 
lots of colors! Lovely colors!
Red, blue, green and yellow
orange, purple and brown 

You will learn about the shapes, 
about the shapes! Funny shapes!
Circle, triangle, rectangle,
heart, square and oval

You will play with rattles and drums,
musical rattles and drums 
You’ll go dum dum dum
and shake tambourines 

You will play on slides and swings
fun slides and swings
You’ll enjoy each and every moment
School’s fun, baby

You will play with toys and blocks,
colorful toys and blocks
You will paint seashells and rocks
You’ll like school, baby

You will read books with lovely stories,
funny stories, happy stories
You’ll have many birthday parties
with your buddies

Soon the day will be over,
school will be over
And you’ll come back home with
me your mommy

It’s the first day of school
first day of school
Come on, let’s go to school
Come on, mommy!
Come on, mommy!
Come on…, mommy!...

Time For A Bath Baby, Time For A Bath
Let’s Take A Warm And Bubbly Bath
A Hot Bath & Shower Can Bring Us Joy
You Can Even Play With Your Favorite Toy

No, No, Mommy, Not Now,
Not Now!

What’s In The Tub, My Baby Dear!
Your Little Toy Puppy Is Swimming Here!
A Bubble Bath Can Be So Great!
Now Jump In The Bath And Don’t Be Late!

No, No, Mommy, Not Now!
Not Now!

Look At The Elephant Bathing Here!
Splashing The Water Far And Near!

Watch Him Splashing With His Trunk And Ear!
He’s Having Such Fun Just Look My Dear!

Look At The Ducks Swimming On Their Backs
Happily Singing Quack, Quack, Quack...
Jump In The Tub My Special One
You Can Take A Bath And Have Lots Of Fun

I Want To Have Fun With All Of You!
So I Will Bathe And Be Clean Too!

playlist_videos.title: The Color Hop Song - ChuChu TV Baby Nursery Rhymes and Kids Songs #babytaku
playlist_videos.description:
Have fun listening to ChuChu TV's songs on Spotify: https://chuchu.me/Spotify

Baby Taku and his buddies are having a blast playing the Color Hop game with their teacher. They're clapping, hopping, dancing, stomping, jumping, and also learning the names of all their favorite colors - red, blue, green, yellow, orange, pink, purple, and brown.

The Color Hop Song Lyrics :

Hi, Kids!
Are you ready to play a fun game?

Yes!

Let’s play a game and hop on colors,
dance on colors, play on colors.
The music stopped, if you’re on this color,
stomp and say its name.

Red!

Correct! Red!

Let’s play a game and hop on colors,
dance on colors, play on colors.
The music stopped, if you’re on this color,
jump and say its name.

Blue!

Yes! Blue!

Let’s play a game and hop on colors,
dance on colors, play on colors.
The music stopped, if you’re on this color,
twirl and say its name.

Green!

Correct! Green!

Let’s play a game and hop on colors,
dance on colors, play on colors.
The music stopped, if you’re on this color,
clap and say its name.

Orange!

Yes! Orange!

Let’s play a game and hop on colors,
dance on colors, play on colors.
The music stopped, if you’re on this color,
wave and say its name.

Purple!

Right! Purple!

Let’s try another color.

Let’s play a game and hop on colors,
dance on colors, play on colors.
The music stopped, if you’re on this color,
wiggle and say its name.

Pink!

Right! Pink!
Come on, let’s play the music again!

Let’s play a game and hop on colors,
dance on colors, play on colors.
The music stopped, if you’re on this color,
fly and say its name.

Yellow!

Yes, Yes!
And now there’s only one color left.
Let’s see who can skip on it and say its name?

Brown!

That’s right! Brown!

playlist_videos.description:
Have fun listening to ChuChu TV's songs on Spotify: https://chuchu.me/Spotify

Baby Taku, ChuChu, and ChaCha go to the circus. They meet clowns and see the circus animals performing tricks. They also watch the circus parade with elephants, bears, monkeys, horses, poodles, hippos, and lions.

Circus Song Lyrics :

Today is the day we go to the circus 
Go to the circus, go to the circus, 
Today is the day we go to the circus 
Haha heehee hoho! 

The circus tent is big and grand 
Big and grand, bright and grand, 
We’ll go in together and hold mommy’s hands 
Haha heehee hoho! 

The clowns at the circus are so funny 
So funny, so funny, 
Their red noses, shoes and hats are so funny 
Haha heehee hoho! 

The elephant at the circus is big and tall 
Big and tall, fat and tall, 
The elephant at the circus rolls on a ball 
Haha heehee hoho! 

The bear at the circus rides on a scooter 
On a scooter, on a scooter 
The bear at the circus is also a juggler 
Haha heehee hoho! 

The monkey at the circus can drive a car 
Drive a car, drive a car, 
The monkey at the circus is a super star 
Haha heehee hoho! 

The horse at the circus can dance, dance, dance, 
Dance, dance, dance! Prance, prance, prance! 
The horse is so good let’s clap our hands 
Haha heehee hoho! 

The poodles at the circus know lots of tricks, 
Many funny tricks! Many clever tricks! 
Some of them can dance and walk on sticks! 
Haha heehee hoho! 

The hippo at the circus dances in a hoop, 
A big round hoop! Hula hoop! 
The hippo at circus is funny and cute 
Haha heehee hoho! 

The lion at the circus jumps through a ring 
Through a ring, through a ring, 
The mighty jumping lion is the circus king 
Haha heehee hoho! 

The children at the circus watch the parade 
The animal parade, the clown parade 
The children clap - the circus is so great 
Haha heehee hoho!

playlist_videos.description:
Have fun listening to ChuChu TV's songs on Spotify: https://chuchu.me/Spotify

Baby Taku, ChuChu, and ChaCha love spending their day helping their mommy with chores. They've realized how hard she works and have decided to help her out more often.

Helping Mommy Song Lyrics :

We’re bored, what do we do?
Very bored, what do we do?
We’ve played games, watched cartoons

Why don’t you help your Mommy?

We are going to help you, Mommy!

Please tell us what to do!
Clean, clean, that’s what we’ll do
Make everything as good as new
Dust and sweep with brushes and brooms
We’ll make everything tidy

What do we do next?

Come on, I’ll show you!

Wash, wash, that’s what we’ll do!
Dry, dry, that’s what we’ll do!
Fold our clothes, polish our shoes!
We’ll keep everything neatly

All the hard work has made me hungry!

Me too!

Come on! You can help me cook!

Peel vegetables is what we’ll do!
Mix and blend, make delicious food!
Toss and stir salad and soup!
Set the table for everybody!

What’s next, Mommy?

Are there any more chores?

Yes! Come on!

Water the garden is what we’ll do!
Keep it neat with our gardening tools
Make the flowers smile and bloom!
We’ll make the garden lovely!

Mommy works so hard, doesn’t she?
We must all help our Mommies.
Not just today but every day.

Hi, kids!
Thanks for helping me today!

Help, help, mommy is what we’ll do!
Helping is a nice thing to do
It’ll make Mommy’s work easy!
And keep us all busy!

I’m proud of you all!
You’ve all been so good and helpful.

Hee hee hee!

Ha ha ha!

playlist_videos.description:

Baby Taku, along with ChuChu and ChaCha, are learning from their mommy about various ways to stay safe when there are germs around. She encourages them to wear face masks, keep their hands and feet clean, and suggests other important things they can do to stay healthy.

Yes Yes Stay Safe Song Lyrics :

Let’s learn, learn, learn, learn, some smart and safe things to do
Yes, yes, yes, Mommy, please tell us what to do

Wear, wear, wear a mask each time you go out
Yes, yes, yes, Mommy, we’ll wear masks when we’re out

Look, look at everything but don’t touch anything
Yes, yes, yes, Mommy, we’ll keep our hands in

Wave, wave but don’t hug, shake hands or high five
Yes, yes, yes, Mommy, we’ll wave hi and bye

Leave, leave your shoes outside when you come home
Yes, yes, yes, Mommy, we’ll leave our shoes at the door

Wash, wash, wash your hands with lots of soap and water
Yes, yes, yes, Mommy, we’re washing with soap and water

Scrub, scrub both your feet and all your toes
Yes, yes, yes, Mommy, we’re scrubbing our feet and toes

Hee hee hee!
Hee hee hee!

Stay, stay, stay at home and have lots of fun
Yes, yes, yes, Mommy, home is a lot of fun

All, all, all, these rules will keep you very safe
Yes, yes, yes, Mommy, all these rules are just great

playlist_videos.description:
Have fun listening to ChuChu TV's songs on Spotify: https://chuchu.me/Spotify

Baby Taku, ChuChu, and ChaCha are having a great time playing and learning about different colors. Mom gives them a color clue and they have to guess what it is. Then, the kids take turns trying to guess what each other are thinking.

I See Colors Song Lyrics :

Red, red, I see some red things - can you see them too?

Yes, yes, I see the red things that you’re seeing too!

The apple, the strawberry and the cherries!
They are all red!

Green, green, I see some green things - can you see them too?

Yes, yes, I see the green things that you’re seeing too!

The caterpillar, the grasshopper and the frog!
They are all green!

Blue, blue, I see some blue things - Can you see them too?

Yes, yes, I see the blue things you’re seeing too!

The sky, the balloon and the truck.
They are blue.

Yellow, yellow, I see some yellow things - can you see them too?

Yes, yes, I can see the yellow things you’re seeing too!

The sun, the sunflower and the hay.
They are all yellow!

Orange, orange, I see some orange things - can you see them too?

Yes, yes, I can see the orange things you’re seeing too!

The orange, the pumpkin and the hat.
They are all orange.

Pink, pink, I see some pink things - Can you see them too?
Yes, yes, I can see the pink things you’re seeing too!

The butterfly, the slide and the rose.
They are all pink.

Brown, brown, I see some brown things - can you see them too?

Yes, yes, I can see the brown things that you’re seeing too!

The chocolate cake, the guitar and the teddy bear.
They are all brown.

Red! Green! Blue!
Yellow! Orange! Pink!
Brown!

playlist_videos.description:

Despite Baby Taku's desire to stay indoors, Mommy takes him to the park and emphasizes how beneficial exercise and fresh air are for his growth. Baby Taku delights in running, jumping, and playing on the park's slides, swings, and jungle gym.

Play Outside Song Lyrics :

One, two, three, and four 
Time to go outdoors 
Let’s go to the park 
Let’s go and play outside!  

Why does Baby have to go outside? 
Can Baby stay inside? 
Can Baby sit on the couch today 
And play with toys, is that ok?  

Fresh air and exercise  
Will help Baby grow! 
Running, jumping, playing outside 
Will make his face smile and glow!   

Baby wants to grow and glow 
Baby wants to be big and strong 
Let’s go and play outside! 
For fresh air and exercise  

Run to the park, run my boy 
There’s so much that you can do 
So many games you can enjoy 
So many things that you can choose! 

Mommy, Mommy, is it okay 
If Baby sits on the side? 
Can Baby sit there on the bench  
Can Baby just sit and watch?  

Look how much fun you can have
Playing flying on the swing 
Up and down on the slide 
And climbing up the jungle gym!  

Baby wants to have fun 
Like all the other kids 
Baby is going to try the swings  
And climb the jungle gym

Baby’s cheeks are rosy red 
With fresh air and exercise  

Baby has had so much fun Playing outside!

Six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

playlist_videos.description:

Santa Claus visits Baby Taku, ChuChu, ChaCha, and their friends on Christmas Eve. He takes them for a ride in his magical flying sleigh, and all the kids help Santa distribute gifts and have plenty of fun.

Jingle Bells - Spirit of Love Song Lyrics:

Merry Christmas!

Jingle bells, jingle bells
Jingle all the way,
Oh what fun it is to ride
In a one-horse open sleigh, Hey!

Jingle bells, jingle bells
Jingle all the way,
Oh what fun it is to ride
In a one-horse open sleigh, Hey!

Dashing through the snow
In a one-horse open sleigh
Through the fields we go
Laughing all the way

Bells on bob-tails ring
Making spirits bright
What fun it is to ride and sing
A sleighing song tonight

Jingle bells, jingle bells
Jingle all the way,
Oh what fun it is to ride
In a one-horse open sleigh

Let us sing, let us sing and
Dance all the way
Lots of Joy and inner peace
Fill our home this day, Hey!

Music’s in the air
No reason for despair
Your life is full of cheer
And your best gifts are right here

Christmas brings us joy
Better than any toy
Let’s all give hugs and care
There’s oh so much to share

Let Peace and joy, Laugh and smiles
Fill your homes today
Let the spirit of love, Fill our hearts
On this Christmas day

Every time you give
It fills your heart with cheer
That’s the way to live
The Christmas spirit’s here

Not just a special day
Or a giving time of year
Christmas is a state of mind
With love and peace right here

Jingle bells, jingle bells
Jingle all the way,
Oh what fun it is to ride
In a one-horse open sleigh

Merry Christmas and Happy New Year!

We like tubbing in the snow.
We like skiing in the snow,
eating smores and hot cocoa.

Snow, snow, wonderful snow.

Snow, snow, cold, icy snow.
We love playing in the snow!

Let’s make pizza, let’s make pizza, yummy pizza.
A big round delicious, tasty pizza.

A big round delicious crispy pizza.
We love pizza, pizza is our favorite treat.
Let’s hurry, pizza is so yummy to eat!

Roll and toss and stretch the dough.
Pat the dough, put it in a pan.
Pat, pat, pat, pat with your little hands.

Pour some sauce, pour some sauce, pizza sauce.
Pour it so nicely all over the top.
Spread the sauce all over with a spoon.
Our pizza will be ready to eat real soon!

Get the cheese, get the cheese, shred some cheese.

Sprinkle all the toppings that you like!
Mushrooms, olives, peppers, make pizza taste nice!
 
Bake the pizza, bake the pizza, in the oven. 
The oven’s hot, never, never put your hands in!
When the dough’s crispy and the cheese has melted nicely. 
We’ll take the pizza out and have a pizza party!

When you first tried to roll over

When you got hurt on your hands and knees

Soon came that moment that made me freeze
Yes you crawled with your hands and knees

When you first tried to walk on your own
It made me curious, but I knew you had grown
When you stumbled and fell on the ground
It made me nervous when I heard that sound
Soon came the moment that made me joyful
Yes you walked around, and I was thankful

Happy Birthday to you my dear
Daddy is here to make you cheer
Your brother, sister and friends are near
They brought some gifts for you my dear
Happy Birthday to you my dear
May god bless you, have a great year

playlist_videos.title: Baby Care and Share Song - ChuChu TV Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs with #BabyTaku
playlist_videos.description:
Have fun listening to ChuChu TV's songs on Spotify: https://chuchu.me/Spotify

Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Baby Taku who didn't want to share his cake with anyone. One day, his daddy showed him a group of crows who were happily sharing their food and taking care of each other. Baby Taku was so inspired by their kindness and realized that sharing is caring. From that day on, he happily started sharing too!

Baby Care and Share Song Lyrics :

Come with me – I've something to show! 
On the tree-top, can you see a big crow? 
There are many more of them sitting in a row! 
What are they doing there? You should know! 
Daddy, I can't see them all! 

Because I am too small! 
The crows are so happy sitting there! 
They joyfully divide their food and share - 
Eating together with love and care! 
Real joy is yours when you share 

They care and share! 
Love is in the air! 
They share and care! 
Isn’t that fair? 
There's real joy when you share! 
So share and care… care and share! 

Daddy I do care care 
I will always share share 
Let's care and share! Love is in the air! 
Share and care! Isn't that fair? 
There's real joy when you share! 
Let's care and share!

playlist_videos.description:

playlist_videos.description:
Have fun listening to ChuChu TV's songs on Spotify: https://chuchu.me/Spotify

. It's time for a snack, but Baby Taku is too engrossed in playing to take a break. His mother gently reminds him that he needs nutritious snacks like fruits, nuts, and milk to help keep his energy levels up.

Snack Time Song Lyrics :

Come my Baby, come my dear 
It’s time for your snack 
Snack time, snack time, snack time, 
It’s Baby’s snack time! 

Mommy, Mommy, why is that? 
Why must Baby have a snack? 
Baby wants to play, play, play! 
No snack for Baby today.   

Baby needs some energy 
To get through the day 
A snack will give him the power he needs 
To jump around and play! 

Baby doesn’t want to be tired 
Feel lazy and cranky  
Baby wants his energy 
A snack for Baby, please!  

Something healthy for Baby to drink,
Something healthy for Baby to munch 
Yummy milk in his favorite cup 
And fruit that go CRUNCH!  

Why must Baby have milk and fruit? 
Can Baby have something else? 
Can Baby have some soda to drink? 
Can Baby have candy to eat?   

Soda and candy are bad for your teeth 
Not good for Baby’s health 
But milk and fruits have vitamins 
That will give him muscles and strength!  

Baby wants to be tough and big 
With strong and shiny teeth 
Baby wants a healthy snack 
Can Baby have fruit and milk, please?

If Baby chooses healthy treats 
Like fruits and nuts and cheese 
He will grow up to be strong and smart 
With muscles as big as mine!  

Baby has finished his milk 
He has finished all his fruit 
With these yummy, healthy treats 
Baby is full of energy!

playlists.playlist_title: Ultimate Toddler Playlist: Adventure, Learning, and Fun - ChuChu TV
playlists.playlist_description:
Welcome to the Ultimate Toddler Playlist, a carefully crafted mix of fun, adventure, and learning, perfect for little ones! This playlist keeps your toddler engaged with a variety of themes that balance learning and play. From exploring animal sounds in the jungle to counting colorful cars, from shape-building fun to dancing along with silly characters, every video brings something new and exciting.

Join Baby Taku, ChuChu, Chiku, Chika, and ChaCha as they embark on imaginative adventures, solve puzzles, sing-along to classic nursery rhymes, and explore the world around them. Whether it's diving under the ocean to meet sea creatures, blasting off into space, or racing vehicles across a construction site, there’s something for every curious mind!

What to Expect:
Animal Adventures, Colorful Learning, and Counting Fun
Dance Parties and Musical Adventures with The Funsters
Imaginative Play and Shape Challenges
Interactive Problem-Solving and Puzzle Time
Exploring Vehicles, Nature, and the World Around Us
With a variety of high-energy moments mixed with calm, thoughtful activities, this playlist is designed to keep toddlers entertained while promoting early learning skills such as counting, problem-solving, and creativity. Get ready to dance, sing, learn, and laugh alongside your favorite characters in this ultimate toddler playlist!

. Here comes "Learning English Is Fun™", a NEW Alphabet Learning Series for Preschool Children from ChuChu TV

English is one of the most widely spoken languages in the world and it is important for children to be fluent in English in order to be able to communicate more effectively and widely. Learning more about the 26 letters of the English alphabets and other concepts will help the young pre-school kids build a strong foundation for
their future reading and verbal skills from an early age. 

The upbeat songs in each episode of Learning English Is Fun© will not just entertain children but also help them strengthen their language, motor, cognitive and social skills. The songs will also work as tools to build critical listening skills, develop sound discrimination and to introduce new vocabulary.
